{
  "page": "Did you know/122",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>... that the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_comet\" title=\"Red comet\">red comet</a> that appears in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> is partially inspired by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caesar%27s_Comet\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Caesar&#39;s Comet\">Caesar's Comet</a> from <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Shakespeare\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:William Shakespeare\">William Shakespeare</a>'s <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julius_Caesar_(play)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Julius Caesar (play)\">Julius Caesar</a></i>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comet_Hale%E2%80%93Bopp\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Comet Hale–Bopp\">Comet Hale–Bopp</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comet_Hyakutake\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Comet Hyakutake\">Comet Hyakutake</a>?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm1214.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm1214.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Did_you_know/122&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rssm1214.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rssm1214.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <i><a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/1214